                  <persName id="t18260406-312-victim1673" type="victimName">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18260406-312-victim1673" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-victim1673" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-victim1673" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-312-off1676 t18260406-312-victim1673"></join>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18260406-312-viclabel1677" type="occupation">fishmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-312-victim1673 t18260406-312-viclabel1677"></join>, and live in Leadenhall-market. The prisoner was employed by me to receive money. On the 7th of March he was sent to receive 10l. 17s. 6d.; he never returned to me, nor accounted to me for it; I saw him again the next night - he did jobs about the market - I had employed him at that time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-312-person1674">
                  JOHN 
                  STALKER
               <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1674" type="surname" value="STALKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1674" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1674" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner called on me on the 7th of March, and asked for some money for Mr. Brown; I gave him a cheque for 10l., a half-sovereign, and seven shillings - he did not give a receipt.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-312-person1675">
                  ROGER 
                  JONATHAN SEABROOK
               <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1675" type="surname" value="JONATHAN SEABROOK"></interp>
