                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1675" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a clerk at Messrs. Hanbury and Co's.; I paid this cheque on the 7th of March.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-312-person1676">
                  GEORGE 
                  WATTS
               <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1676" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1676" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1676" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was informed that the prisoner had absconded, and went to Brunswick-place, New Kent-road, at nine o'clock at night, on the 8th of March - I found him in bed - there was a woman and child in the room; he delivered to Knight 9l. 13s. 6d.; I asked what he had done with the cheque; he said he had changed it, and laid some out in a pair of shoes, a shirt, and a pair of stockings.</p>
               <p>COURT to 
               <persName id="t18260406-312-person1677">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18260406-312-person1677" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
